Follow these conventions

1. Use xstate with state machines
2. Maintain the component logic separate from machine logic, the logic should be only in state machines.
3. We need to have a component as per the following structure:
Component
    - Component.tsx
    - Component.scss
    - machine
        - index.ts
        - machine.ts
        - actors.ts
        - guards.ts
        - actions.ts
        - types.ts
- actors contain all the service calls. So, we shouldn't import the actors, guards etc. in machine.ts, they should be passed using index.ts using machine.provide

eg.
const machine = createMachine({
    id: "machine",
    initial...
    context: ({input}):...
    states:{
        ...
    }
    // if using ac=pi calls,
    fetchUsers:{
        invoke:{
            src: "fetchUsers",
            input: ({context, event}=>{
                
            },
            onDone:{},....)
        }
    }
})
export default assignLotMachine;

index.ts

export default (additionalActions) =>
machine.provide({actions: .{..actions, ...additionalActions},
actors, guards});

actors.ts
export const fetchUsers = fromPromise(
    async ({input}):{
        const url = getApplicationTypeUrl;
        return fetcherget(url).then()...
    }
)

Inside component,

const [state, send] = useMachine(machine({dismiss}), {
    input:{
        a: 2
    }
})

Use state.matches send({type: "ASSIGN", data: {...}})

4. Check for labels.ts - in locale -> en -> labels in which exported labels are present. Use the labels in headers etc. like local("allocation.id") - locale.ts has default localeParser

5. Use index/constants for constants and index/utils for utils

6. Whenever making an api call, use mappers. Write a mapped fetcher and use it everywhere instead of fetcher.

7. If a component can be reuseable or its a separate component, it has to be under /components folder

8. After everything, maintain a file called app_guide and update the info all the info about the app so that the next time I use agent, it can continue reading about the app and get the understanding of the entire application.
